patterns_discovered.description: Work is organized by sessions with numbered progression (session 2→4), suggesting parallel or iterative task execution

patterns_discovered.description: Project transitions through defined phases (Verification → Testing with increasing phase totals)

recommendations.recommendation: Document the session numbering strategy and explain why sessions skip numbers (e.g., parallel execution, deleted sessions)
recommendations.rationale: Prevent confusion about workflow state and enable better debugging

recommendations.recommendation: Add timestamps to individual subtask completions within a session to understand task granularity
recommendations.rationale: Current status file only shows session-level timestamps; subtask-level timing would reveal bottlenecks

recommendations.recommendation: Ensure login flow testing covers both successful and failure paths (incorrect credentials, session handling, etc.)
recommendations.rationale: Current task only validates 'successful login flow' - comprehensive testing requires failure scenarios

recommendations.recommendation: Consider adding status file changes to .gitignore or automated commit patterns to standardize tracking
recommendations.rationale: Status file appears to be auto-updated; clarify whether it should be version controlled or generated
